&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have a variety of exciting nursing opportunities both full and part time in Medicineat Ipswich Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have opportunities in:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Assessment Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respiratory Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stroke Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cardiology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7 day Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endocrine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You&#39;ll be working with friendly, motivated, supportive teams to provide excellent patient care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer great opportunities for learning and development to enable you to meet your career goals. We are happy to discuss rotational posts so you can get the most out of your experience working with us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have invested in a new respiratory unit and are currently building a new Ambulatory Medical Same Day Emergency Care unit. We should start work on a new Urgent&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Treatment Centre in 2021 so it&#39;s a great time to join us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Becky May, Senior Matron - becky.may@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
